'Fribourg' (; , ; or Freiburg im [[Ãechtland]], Swiss German
pronunciation: ; or Friborgo) is the capital of the Swiss canton of
Fribourg and the district of Sarine. It is located on both sides of the river
Saane/Sarine, on the Swiss plateau, and is an important economic, administrative
and educational center on the cultural border between German and French
Switzerland (Romandy). Its Old City, one of the best maintained in Switzerland,
sits on a small rocky hill above the valley of the Sarine.
